		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm into homebrew because I've had an interest in game dev ever since I started programming. I'm attracted to the NES specifically (and retro systems generally) because it's possible for one developer or a small team to actually produce a finished game that's on the same level as commercial releases. On modern consoles and the PC that's hardly possible anymore.

		

