	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A long time ago, I was writing simple puzzle games for the Apple II in BASIC with assembly language subroutines. (The NES's CPU uses the same instruction set as the Apple II's CPU.)
<br />
<br />Fast forward to years later when I was CHR-hacking SMB1 to replace Mario with different characters. Then I tried to hack Contra but discovered that its graphics were compressed, so instead I decided to try to write my own platformer. Obviously, other things intervened, and the puzzle games I wrote to familiarize myself with the platform ended up taking over.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


